article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 70, Monmouth, N.J. 66
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Sean Baptiste scored 23 points and pulled down 10 rebounds as Fairleigh Dickinson rallied for a 70-66 win over Monmouth on Friday night. Manny Ubilla added 20 points and Bernell Murray finished with 13 for the Knights (6-11, 2-5 in Northeast Conference). Whitney Coleman had 21 points and eight rebounds for the Hawks (5-15, 2-6), while R.J. Rutledge chipped in 15 points. FDU trailed 41-36 at the break and was down by as many as nine points midway through the second half, but earned the win by outscoring Monmouth 17-4 in the final seven minutes. Ubilla's 3-pointer with 1:28 left gave FDU the lead for good, and Baptiste then sealed the win by hitting 3-of-4 free throws in the final 22 seconds.
